                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12893926" author="stack" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2010 03:59:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why not just run N rowcounter MR jobs?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12893927" author="ted_yu" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2010 04:10:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My plan is to accept regex as table names and use MetaScanner.metaScan() to discover the tables.&lt;br/&gt;
The goal is to calculate the total number of rows across all those tables.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I came upon this requirement when investigating &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2885&quot; title=&quot;Data which was invisible shows up after restarting HBase&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2885&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2885&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12894096" author="ted_yu" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2010 18:20:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;TableInputFormatBase in both namespaces only keeps reference to HTable.&lt;br/&gt;
An HTable array needs to be used for this request.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
